1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,620
So this will be a fun class today.

2
00:00:02,760 --> 00:00:04,780
We are doing the Great Pyramid.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:07,440
Okay, so

4
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:10,280
the Great Pyramid was

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:13,800
built about 2500 BCE,

6
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:16,020
that's 4500 years ago,

7
00:00:16,160 --> 00:00:19,260
by a pharaoh named Curfew.

8
00:00:20,540 --> 00:00:23,920
And it was one of the

9
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:29,460
seven great wonders of the ancient world.

10
00:00:29,660 --> 00:00:31,560
It's the only one that's still standing.

11
00:00:32,980 --> 00:00:38,540
From 2500 until 1400 CE,

12
00:00:38,760 --> 00:00:39,740
which is about 4000 years,

13
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,560
it was the tallest

14
00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:46,860
man -made building in the world.

15
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:50,960
Okay? Okay? The Great Pyramid,

16
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:53,320
the direction is true north,

17
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:59,000
meaning you can actually use the pyramids
as a compass to tell the directions.

18
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:05,620
Let's look at the architecture
of the Great Pyramid.

19
00:01:05,980 --> 00:01:09,900
So the center is something
called the King's Chamber.

20
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:13,880
That's where the King's mummy
rests in the sarcophagus.

21
00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:19,240
There's a grand gallery that gives
you access to the King's Chamber.

22
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:21,120
And then a slope.

23
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,440
And then it's a pyramid structure.

24
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:27,920
And on the top of the pyramid
is what is called the Ben -Ben.

25
00:01:29,300 --> 00:01:34,760
Or the Pyrrhonion.

26
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,920
Okay? The Pyrrhonion.

27
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:41,460
Okay? And it is extremely significant
culturally and religiously in Egypt.

28
00:01:41,740 --> 00:01:44,060
Because in Egyptian mythology,

29
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:47,720
the religion, the creator god, Atum,

30
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:50,720
he's known as Atum, he's also
known as Ra, the sun god,

31
00:01:52,260 --> 00:01:55,580
first came into existence on the Ben -Ben.

32
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:59,200
So imagine a large dark ocean.

33
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:04,160
And there's nothing. And then
suddenly emerges a mound.

34
00:02:04,360 --> 00:02:05,740
Okay? Called a Ben -Ben.

35
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,960
And that's where comes
the creator god, Atum.

36
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,300
Or Ra. Okay?

37
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:16,480
That's one legend. The other legend
is from the dark ocean of space,

38
00:02:16,480 --> 00:02:19,480
comes down a Ben -Ben.

39
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,940
And on top of it rests Atum.

40
00:02:24,060 --> 00:02:28,260
Okay? So this idea of the
Pyrrhonion, the Ben -Ben,

41
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:34,060
it is central to the idea of
creation in Egyptian mythology.

42
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,700
So this is an extremely powerful

43
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:40,540
and

44
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:44,080
beautiful monument to Egyptian culture.

45
00:02:45,820 --> 00:02:48,840
Architecturally, Napoleon,
who visited the Great Pyramid,

46
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:50,640
he calculated that

47
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:53,780
if you took all the stones
from the Great Pyramid,

48
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:57,240
you could actually build a wall
around the perimeter of France.

49
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:04,540
There's more material in the Great
Pyramid except for two structures.

50
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,280
The first structure is
the Great Wall of China.

51
00:03:06,440 --> 00:03:08,380
There's more stone in
the Great Wall of China.

52
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,060
Okay? There's more stone,

53
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:13,780
there's more material in
the Great Three Gorges Dam.

54
00:03:13,780 --> 00:03:16,040
Also in China. Okay?

55
00:03:16,160 --> 00:03:21,520
And it took about 26 years
to build this pyramid.

56
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:25,920
So today, in today's class, I'm
going to look at three questions.

57
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:29,420
The first question is,
how did they build this?

58
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:32,080
Because it's still with us today.

59
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:35,380
You can actually go to Egypt
and visit the Great Pyramid.

60
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:39,540
Second question is, why
did they build this?

61
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:42,880
What was the purpose? And
the third question is,

62
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,440
why did they stop building the pyramids?

63
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:50,560
Okay? So those are the three
questions we're looking at today.

64
00:03:51,220 --> 00:03:53,620
How was it built? Why was it built?

65
00:03:53,820 --> 00:03:57,840
And why did the Egyptians
stop building the pyramids?

66
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:03,320
So, how it was built is an
extremely controversial question

67
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:06,480
that has plagued historians
and Egyptologists

68
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:10,200
and archaeologists for hundreds of years.

69
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:13,780
Okay? And

70
00:04:13,780 --> 00:04:18,040
originally, a Greek historian,
Herodotus, proposed the idea

71
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,620
the pyramid was built in steps.

72
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,460
Okay? So it was first a
step pyramid, and then

73
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:25,980
using pulleys, they pulled the stones up.

74
00:04:26,320 --> 00:04:30,840
Okay? And it was the accepted
idea for the longest time.

75
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,240
There was no better idea.

76
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:35,620
But architecturally,
that has been disproven.

77
00:04:35,740 --> 00:04:38,740
Okay? It can't work that way. Then,

78
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:43,740
about ten years ago, there was a French
architect named John Pierre Houdin.

79
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:47,280
Okay? H -O -U -D -I -N, Houdin.

80
00:04:47,740 --> 00:04:49,920
And he's an architect.
He's never been to Egypt.

81
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:52,400
Doesn't speak Arabic. Never studied Egypt.

82
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:55,200
But his father and

83
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:59,240
him were very interested in how
the Great Pyramid was constructed.

84
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:00,900
So he came up with this theory.

85
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:05,560
And they've run computer simulations
and discovered this to be true.

86
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:08,760
There's also a lot of physical evidence
to suggest this theory is true.

87
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:11,000
Okay? So this is how they
built the Great Pyramid.

88
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,420
What they did was,

89
00:05:12,460 --> 00:05:17,600
they first constructed an external
ramp in order to build the base.

90
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,860
Okay? So you now have the base.

91
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:25,020
And then from the base, what they did was,

92
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:29,320
they built two structures.

93
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:32,600
Okay? And this is what
they call counterweights.

94
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:35,640
Okay? So these counterweights
are like pulleys, which

95
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:40,140
allows them to pull
the stones up, up high.

96
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,420
Okay? And then

97
00:05:41,420 --> 00:05:44,480
surrounding these two structures is what

98
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:47,720
they call an eternal spiral ramp.

99
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,580
Okay? To carry the stones up.

100
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:56,160
And so what they did was, they basically
built the pyramids from the inside out.

101
00:05:57,540 --> 00:05:59,380
And then once they built the structure,

102
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:02,380
they covered it up with limestone.

103
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:07,020
So that it reflects in the sun.

104
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,120
Okay? If you actually were living with
a person, you would have a limestone.

105
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:13,500
But if you were living back then, and
you saw the pyramids from a distance,

106
00:06:13,700 --> 00:06:18,060
you would think it was the star that
has come down on the planet Earth.

107
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:21,260
Okay? So

108
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:24,900
that's how they built the pyramid.

109
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:28,060
But then this raises another
interesting question,

110
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:31,760
is how they come up with this plan.

111
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:35,740
And how were they able to
do this without blueprints

112
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:40,120
and without basically writing,
or modern engineering techniques?

113
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:44,660
And the answer is, if you think
about it, what they did was,

114
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:47,180
they built a model right
beside the pyramid,

115
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:52,080
which allowed them to figure out
how to build a larger pyramid.

116
00:06:52,280 --> 00:06:56,080
Okay? But,

117
00:06:56,080 --> 00:06:58,960
inontologists still believe
this was not possible,

118
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,860
because they believe that

119
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:06,420
Egyptians didn't have the intellectual
capacity to imagine this to be true.

120
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:09,980
Okay? And I'll show you later
on that they actually did,

121
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:14,920
that we underestimate their imagination
and their intellectual capacity.

122
00:07:15,320 --> 00:07:18,700
So that answers the first question
pretty easily, how is it built?

123
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:22,420
A more controversial
question is why was it built?

124
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:24,740
And for the longest time,

125
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:29,380
the accepted theory is this is a tomb,

126
00:07:30,140 --> 00:07:35,900
a tomb. The reason why is Egyptians
believed in the afterlife.

127
00:07:36,840 --> 00:07:40,900
And so the theory is
this pyramid is designed

128
00:07:41,690 --> 00:07:45,580
to ease the Pharaoh's
transition into the heavens

129
00:07:45,890 --> 00:07:49,680
where he would become a star or a sun.

130
00:07:51,280 --> 00:07:55,760
And so the common phrase is this
is almost a resurrection machine

131
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:58,820
where the Pharaoh goes up to the sky

132
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:00,560
and then after a few centuries,

133
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:05,080
he reincarnates inside the pyramid.

134
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:09,020
And the structure is
meant to accomplish this.

135
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:12,860
And again, this is the generally
accepted theory today.

136
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:21,100
But there are three major
problems with this theory

137
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:26,280
which basically makes it,
which basically discounts it.

138
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:31,060
The first major problem is
there are about 100 pyramids

139
00:08:32,120 --> 00:08:35,060
in Egypt. 100 or more.

140
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,320
We don't know, okay?

141
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,600
We have not found a mummy

142
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:45,460
or a body inside any
sarcophagus inside the pyramids.

143
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,680
So this is a problem.

144
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,300
If this is a tomb,

145
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:51,460
why is there no body?

146
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,320
We can't find the body, okay?

147
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:56,340
So that's one problem.
Second problem is this.

148
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,120
For this to be a tomb, this implies

149
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:05,000
that the Pharaoh, because the
Pharaoh's so divine, right?

150
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,120
They are basically the
emanation of God on earth.

151
00:09:09,640 --> 00:09:12,460
This means that when they
come to the planet earth

152
00:09:12,460 --> 00:09:17,020
and they come to Pharaoh, their
priority is to build their own tomb,

153
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,520
right?

154
00:09:18,620 --> 00:09:21,360
Does that make any sense? They come
to earth and they're like, okay,

155
00:09:21,400 --> 00:09:24,520
well I'm gonna die so I wanna get
out of here as soon as possible

156
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,920
so let's build our tomb, right?

157
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:30,740
Now the problem is that this would imply

158
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:34,920
that the Pharaoh sees the
Egyptian people as his slave.

159
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:40,060
You exist in order for me to live.

160
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,940
And so,

161
00:09:49,660 --> 00:09:53,520
but the problem is that
in Egyptian mythology,

162
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:57,720
gods are considered
benefactors of the human race.

163
00:09:58,060 --> 00:10:01,180
So for example, Atum -Ra, he is the one

164
00:10:01,180 --> 00:10:04,180
who gave life to the
world, but then his son,

165
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:08,460
his descendant Osiris, another
god, gave civilization to Egypt.

166
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:11,400
And then Horus, the son of Osiris,

167
00:10:11,460 --> 00:10:14,840
gave the institution of
kingship to Egypt. So

168
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:17,440
these gods come to earth in order

169
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:21,980
to help the human race
develop in some capacity.

170
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:24,860
So it doesn't make any sense that

171
00:10:24,860 --> 00:10:27,160
the Pharaoh's primary purpose when

172
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:30,580
he's on earth is to create a tomb
because that's a very selfish reason.

173
00:10:31,540 --> 00:10:32,960
Does that make sense?

174
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:37,840
And the third problem with
this is just pure logic.

175
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:42,200
If you're a Pharaoh and your
primary concern is the afterlife,

176
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:44,600
resurrecting yourself, and

177
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,940
the pyramid is a primary
means of accomplishing this,

178
00:10:47,180 --> 00:10:51,560
and it takes about 26 years or
30 years to build a pyramid,

179
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:55,740
how can you be sure that

180
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:58,860
you won't die before the pyramid is built?

181
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:05,260
Right? That's a problem.

182
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:09,740
So these are three logical problems.

183
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,940
But again, Egyptologists insist that

184
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:16,340
it is a tomb, primarily because of the way

185
00:11:16,340 --> 00:11:18,080
that Egyptians understand the afterlife.

186
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,800
So here's some evidence
to suggest it is a tomb.

187
00:11:22,100 --> 00:11:24,280
This is considered

188
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:29,160
a writing of a Pharaoh to
his son about the pyramid.

189
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:34,280
So this is what he says. Make
your grave well furnished

190
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:36,340
and prepare thy place in the west.

191
00:11:36,940 --> 00:11:38,920
The west is where they go off to die.

192
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,020
Look, death counts little for us.

193
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:46,420
We can conquer death. Look,
life is valued highly by us.

194
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:47,820
We want to become immortal.

195
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:51,780
The house of the dead,
meaning the tomb, is for life.

196
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:54,920
So the pyramid is what
will make us immortal.

197
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:59,800
So this is, again, highly debated today.

198
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:03,240
So logically speaking, it
doesn't make sense that

199
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:06,800
the pyramids are a tomb, but there's a
lot of evidence to suggest it is a tomb.

200
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,100
And because of this debate,

201
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:13,600
different theories have been
proposed as to the purpose of the

202
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:18,160
pyramid. And there are lots of
really strange theories out there.

203
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,840
OK? Lots of really strange theories.

204
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:25,160
One really interesting theory was
proposed by a man named Nikola Tesla,

205
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:28,840
the founder, the creator
of electricity, basically.

206
00:12:28,860 --> 00:12:30,580
And his idea was this.

207
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:34,760
He studied the architecture of the pyramid

208
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:39,880
and he proposed the pyramid
was a battery system,

209
00:12:40,020 --> 00:12:43,860
OK, in order to create free

210
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:55,220
clean energy. And the theory is this, OK?

211
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:59,060
The theory is, first of all, if
you look at the King's Chamber,

212
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:03,620
the sound frequency in it is F sharp.

213
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:07,880
And F sharp is also the
frequency of planet Earth.

214
00:13:08,100 --> 00:13:12,480
OK? So it seems like the pyramid
is attuned to the planet Earth.

215
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:16,900
Second of all, if you look at

216
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:18,420
where

217
00:13:18,420 --> 00:13:22,080
the pyramids are geographically,

218
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:23,580
it's true north.

219
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,920
OK? It's put in a place that

220
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:29,700
matches the directions
of the Earth. And so

221
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:33,320
the theory is the direction of the pyramid

222
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:37,000
is capturing the energy from
the electromagnetic field

223
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,220
that the Earth generates.

224
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:43,420
OK? And the third explanation is inside

225
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:47,620
the pyramids are granite stones
and outside are limestones.

226
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:51,660
And this is a perfect way
to trap and store energy.

227
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,000
OK? So think of a solar panel where

228
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:58,200
the Sun and the Moon reflects
light onto the pyramids

229
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:01,720
and this energy stored inside the pyramid.

230
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:06,120
Okay? And so this is a great theory.

231
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:09,420
And again, there are lots of
people who believe in this because

232
00:14:09,420 --> 00:14:12,380
this is actually much more plausible

233
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:14,300
than the tomb theory.

234
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:17,660
But the problem with this, of course,
is it doesn't work scientifically.

235
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:22,020
And also you have the question of, if
they produce all this free, clean energy,

236
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:25,780
what are they using it for? Okay?

237
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:28,960
So this leads us with a big question.

238
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:32,340
Why did they build the Great Pyramid?

239
00:14:32,880 --> 00:14:36,440
And today I want to propose
to you another solution.

240
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,780
The solution is this.

241
00:14:39,420 --> 00:14:42,580
My belief is the Great Pyramid

242
00:14:42,580 --> 00:14:46,700
was designed as Egypt's Manhattan Project.

243
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:55,620
Okay? The Manhattan
Project, as you know, uh,

244
00:14:55,780 --> 00:14:59,060
was a World War II project in
order to build the nuclear bomb.

245
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:04,640
And you can argue, nuclear bomb is
humanity's greatest invention ever.

246
00:15:05,500 --> 00:15:07,360
It took about 130,000 people

247
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:09,460
over five to six years

248
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:13,040
working in the United
